      "\n  have h‚āĀ : ‚ü™x, a y‚üę_‚Ąā = (toComplexMeasure (toResolutionOfIdentity ha) x y).integral\n    (Function.Embedding.subtype (spectrum ‚Ąā a)) := by\n    -- we need to show that the inner product can be represented as an integral with respect to the complex measure\n    -- First, we use the spectral theorem for self-adjoint operators to express `a` as an integral of the identity function against the resolution of the identity\n    -- Then, we need to evaluate the inner product of `x` and `a y` in terms of this resolution of the identity\n    -- Finally, we use the fact that the integral of the identity function against the complex measure constructed from the resolution of the identity gives us the inner product\n    -- This requires detailed steps involving the completeness of the Hilbert space and the properties of the resolution of the identity\n    sorry\n  -- The result follows directly from the above steps\n  exact h‚āĀ",
